cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the formal analysis of large-scale networks, specifically finite automata networks, and proposes a novel algorithm for identifying sets of local states necessary for reachability. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for identifying cut sets, which could potentially fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm proposed involves graph theory and computation, which could also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
